               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; partly names of the donors; groups of lines in the incipit page of Texts I-I and I-4b; incipit of sections; elements of the punctuation signs and of the text dividers; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>Text I-2 includes the hymns:</note>
                     <note>- ʾO-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä Maryam wäladitä ʾamlak ... "O my Lady Mary, Godbearing ..." (fol. 5va-vb)</note>
                     <note>- ʾO-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä qǝddǝst dǝngǝl bä-kǝlʾe Maryam Mariham ʾǝmmu lä-ʾIyäsus Krǝstos kähali ... "O my Lady, Holy Two-fold Virgin Mary, Mother of Jesus Christ the Almighty ..."(fol. 5vb) (cp. ChRep no. 373)</note>
                     <note>- ʾO-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä qǝddǝst Maryam ʾǝmmä mädḫǝn wä-ʾǝmmä bǝrhan ... "O my Lady, Holy Virgin Mary, Mother of the Saviour and Mother of the Light ..." (fol. 6ra-vb).</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>Text I-5 is distributed as follows: strophes 12-13 (fols. 37ra-39rb); strophes 14-19 (fols. 49ra-56vb); strophes 20-26 (fols. 72va-83va); strophes 27-29 (fols. 17ra-24va); strophes 30-31, 33 (fols. 11ra-14rb).</note>
                  </msItem>
